# Ubuntu 22.04 (Jammy) vulnerabilities from the Playwright base image.
# No patches available from upstream. None affect this action — see reasons below.
# Re-evaluate when upgrading the base image or when Ubuntu publishes fixes.

# coreutils — chroot escape; not applicable, action does not use chroot
CVE-2016-2781

# libpcre3 — regex stack exhaustion; not invoked with untrusted patterns
CVE-2017-11164

# libcairo — requires crafted font files or SVG input; action only processes trusted user-owned .c4 files
CVE-2017-7475
CVE-2018-18064
CVE-2019-6461

# libopenjp2-7 — JPEG 2000 codec DoS; action never processes JPEG 2000 files
CVE-2019-6988
CVE-2023-39328
CVE-2023-39329

